comment.body:
@Bot: I think he will tend to archive them as optional files. No need to worry about that cos you're free to snapshot all things, migrate then. 
ZeroNet is website-based, so it has to have file(html, js, css...) transfer/verification ability. Using this ability to deal with user data is easier to implement and reduces complexity. So json is there. You're free to implement it as db-based completely, but you have a lot of work to do and will not add much benefit on it. 
ZeroMe is not a good place to discuss in-depth. You're free to clone a ZeroTalk to let people discuss there, with very large quota. Paste your post link of your clone forum in official ZeroTalk and ZeroMe to attract people to discuss there.
